{"title_page": "Idiothele", "text_new": "{{Short description| Genus of spiders}}\n{{Automatic taxobox\n| taxon = Idiothele\n| image = imirb.jpg\n| image_caption = Mature female Idiothele mira - Quentin Salinas\n| authority = Hewitt, 1919<ref name=NMBE />\n| type_species = ''[[Idiothele nigrofulva|I. nigrofulva]]''\n| type_species_authority = ([[Reginald Innes Pocock|Pocock]], 1898)\n| subdivision_ranks = Species\n| subdivision = {{Specieslist\n| [[Idiothele mira|I. mira]]|<small>Gallon, 2010</small> \u2013 [[South Africa]]\n| [[Idiothele nigrofulva|I. nigrofulva]]|<small>(Pocock, 1898)</small> \u2013 Southern Africa}}\n}}\n'''''Idiothele''''' is a [[genus]] of African [[Theraphosidae|tarantulas]] that was first described by J. Hewitt in 1919.<ref name=Hewi1919>{{cite journal| last=Hewitt| first=J.| year=1919| title=Descriptions of new South African Araneae and Solifugae| journal=Annals of the Transvaal Museum| pages=63\u2013111| volume=6}}</ref> {{as of|2020|03}} it contains two species, both found in southern Africa: ''[[Idiothele mira|I. mira]]'' and ''[[Idiothele nigrofulva|I. nigrofulva]]''.<ref name=NMBE>{{cite web| title=Gen. Idiothele Hewitt, 1919| website=World Spider Catalog Version 20.0| accessdate=2020-04-17| year=2020| publisher=Natural History Museum Bern| url=http://www.wsc.nmbe.ch/genus/3374| doi=10.24436/2}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Theraphosidae species]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar| from=Q3014044}}\n\n[[Category:Mygalomorphae genera]]\n[[Category:Spiders of Africa]]\n[[Category:Theraphosidae]]\n\n\n{{Theraphosidae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Short description| Genus of spiders}}\n{{Automatic taxobox\n| taxon = Idiothele\n| authority = Hewitt, 1919<ref name=NMBE />\n| type_species = ''[[Idiothele nigrofulva|I. nigrofulva]]''\n| type_species_authority = ([[Reginald Innes Pocock|Pocock]], 1898)\n| subdivision_ranks = Species\n| subdivision = {{Specieslist\n| [[Idiothele mira|I. mira]]|<small>Gallon, 2010</small> \u2013 [[South Africa]]\n| [[Idiothele nigrofulva|I. nigrofulva]]|<small>(Pocock, 1898)</small> \u2013 Southern Africa}}\n}}\n'''''Idiothele''''' is a [[genus]] of African [[Theraphosidae|tarantulas]] that was first described by J. Hewitt in 1919.<ref name=Hewi1919>{{cite journal| last=Hewitt| first=J.| year=1919| title=Descriptions of new South African Araneae and Solifugae| journal=Annals of the Transvaal Museum| pages=63\u2013111| volume=6}}</ref> {{as of|2020|03}} it contains two species, both found in southern Africa: ''[[Idiothele mira|I. mira]]'' and ''[[Idiothele nigrofulva|I. nigrofulva]]''.<ref name=NMBE>{{cite web| title=Gen. Idiothele Hewitt, 1919| website=World Spider Catalog Version 20.0| accessdate=2020-04-17| year=2020| publisher=Natural History Museum Bern| url=http://www.wsc.nmbe.ch/genus/3374| doi=10.24436/2}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Theraphosidae species]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar| from=Q3014044}}\n\n[[Category:Mygalomorphae genera]]\n[[Category:Spiders of Africa]]\n[[Category:Theraphosidae]]\n\n\n{{Theraphosidae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Sesamehoneytart", "label": "safe", "comment": "replaced infobox picture", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idiothele"}
